00:41:54,420 --> 00:41:55,820
should be reinforced.

527
00:41:56,420 --> 00:42:00,180
I would say, "Owing to my tactful
guidance".

528
00:42:00,980 --> 00:42:02,500
- Mine?
- Yours.

529
00:42:03,260 --> 00:42:04,660
Right.

530
00:42:15,420 --> 00:42:17,260
Attention everybody.

531
00:42:17,660 --> 00:42:20,260
Let me read the draft
of my future speech.

532
00:42:25,820 --> 00:42:27,780
Comrades Muscovites!

533
00:42:28,180 --> 00:42:30,100
You see before you

534
00:42:30,340 --> 00:42:33,740
a formidable body
of amateur talent

535
00:42:34,420 --> 00:42:36,540
mostly raised

536
00:42:37,180 --> 00:42:40,100
within my system

537
00:42:41,060 --> 00:42:46,020
owing to my tactful guidance.

538
00:42:47,540 --> 00:42:50,740
- What do you say?
- Good. For you.

539
00:43:08,180 --> 00:43:12,540
Don't you think I should
emphasize the thesis

540
00:43:13,580 --> 00:43:15,940
on my tactful guidance?

541
00:43:16,420 --> 00:43:19,860
We are rehearsing the Musical
Moment by Schubert

542
00:43:20,660 --> 00:43:22,460
and you are interfering.

543
00:43:23,700 --> 00:43:25,660
What do you mean interfering?

544
00:43:26,060 --> 00:43:29,300
Do you mean the moment
of my guidance

545
00:43:29,900 --> 00:43:33,140
is less important
than the Musical Moment

546
00:43:33,580 --> 00:43:35,180
by Schulbert?

547
00:44:38,620 --> 00:44:41,140
The golden mist is playing
in the air.

548
00:44:41,500 --> 00:44:44,100
Oh, youthful joy,
you are beyond belief.

549
00:44:44,340 --> 00:44:47,060
High as the sky,
Vast as the sea

550
00:44:47,220 --> 00:44:49,740
Is our young road indeed.

551
00:44:50,140 --> 00:44:52,420
Sing everybody.

552
00:44:53,220 --> 00:44:55,500
Sing everybody.

553
00:44:56,020 --> 00:44:58,780
High as the sky,
Vast as the sea

554
00:44:59,220 --> 00:45:01,260
Is our young road indeed.

555
00:46:01,580 --> 00:46:03,420
WOODCUTTER

556
00:46:27,700 --> 00:46:30,340
Everything that we have dreamt of
is a-coming true.

557
00:46:30,580 --> 00:46:33,300
To the sun our ambitions
are a-breaking through.

558
00:46:33,580 --> 00:46:36,460
We'll awaken everyone,
We'll get everything we plan.

559
00:46:36,860 --> 00:46:39,140
Like an ear our exuberance
is ripening.

560
00:46:39,380 --> 00:46:41,780
Sing everybody.

561
00:46:42,420 --> 00:46:44,860
Sing everybody.

562
00:46:45,100 --> 00:46:48,100
We'll awaken everyone,
We'll get everything we plan.

563
00:46:48,220 --> 00:46:50,740
Like an ear our exuberance
is ripening.

564
00:46:56,740 --> 00:46:59,540
Our young legs beg for dancing
And we dance with zest.

565
00:46:59,740 --> 00:47:02,580
Our songs are ringing clear
without letup or rest.

566
00:47:02,780 --> 00:47:05,380
Come out, girl,
Look at your beau

567
00:47:05,500 --> 00:47:08,060
And bandy merry words of jest.

568
00:47:27,860 --> 00:47:30,740
- A rousing act.
- They sing well.

569
00:47:30,980 --> 00:47:32,340
Well.

570
00:47:32,780 --> 00:47:35,220
Yes, well. Good on them.

571
00:47:35,540 --> 00:47:36,980
Good on them.

572
00:47:38,100 --> 00:47:39,380
Bad on them.

573
00:47:43,140 --> 00:47:44,420
Shallow-waterers!

574
00:47:44,940 --> 00:47:47,820
- What's going on?
- They're overtaking us.

575
00:47:48,060 --> 00:47:49,340
Bastards.

576
00:47:50,700 --> 00:47:52,100
Full steam!

577
00:47:53,500 --> 00:47:55,740
Comrades, they are overtaking us.

578
00:47:56,420 --> 00:47:58,020
Impostors!

579
00:48:03,540 --> 00:48:05,980
If they get to Moscow before us

580
00:48:06,260 --> 00:48:08,300
our region will be disgraced.

581
00:48:08,900 --> 00:48:10,180
Full steam!

582
00:48:10,620 --> 00:48:12,420
- Full steam!
- Full steam!

583
00:48:12,900 --> 00:48:15,420
- Full steam ahead!
- Fullest steam!

584
00:48:15,860 --> 00:48:17,420
Fullest steam!

585
00:48:17,500 --> 00:48:20,100
Two guys won't cope.

586
00:48:20,860 --> 00:48:22,940
We need help.

587
00:48:23,500 --> 00:48:24,940
Comrades!

588
00:48:27,700 --> 00:48:30,620
Let's help our stokers.

589
00:48:34,940 --> 00:48:36,580
To the fire-chambers, my friends!

590
00:48:39,820 --> 00:48:41,220
To the fire-chambers!

591
00:49:24,540 --> 00:49:25,940
Alyosha!

592
00:49:26,780 --> 00:49:28,100
Alyosha!

593
00:49:34,500 --> 00:49:36,380
Hey, add more steam!

594
00:49:38,860 --> 00:49:41,180
Speed up, you mustached devil.

595
00:49:42,260 --> 00:49:43,580
Do it!

596
00:49:45,100 --> 00:49:48,220
- They're leaving us behind!
- Do something!

597
00:50:13,500 --> 00:50:15,260
Why did we stop?

598
00:50:15,580 --> 00:50:18,180
We are out of gas.

599
00:50:18,380 --> 00:50:20,300
No wind.

600
00:51:05,940 --> 00:51:07,260
Am I in a stew!

601
00:51:10,940 --> 00:51:12,300
Hey there.

602
00:51:14,500 --> 00:51:18,700
Those racers wanted to outdo
a two-funnel giant.

603
00:51:19,260 --> 00:51:22,900
No way, baby. You can't go far
without a funnel.

604
00:51:31,500 --> 00:51:34,420
And we can well use one.

605
00:51:35,140 --> 00:51:36,500
Full steam!

606
00:51:44,180 --> 00:51:46,020
Fourth day

607
00:51:48,220 --> 00:51:50,220
The Kama. The Volga.

608
00:52:09,080 --> 00:52:12,960
I'm a sailor, I've been places,
Navigated lots of vessels.

609
00:52:13,600 --> 00:52:17,520
But I never told a lie,
I am not that kind of guy.

610
00:52:18,080 --> 00:52:22,240
Yes, I'll never tell a lie,
I am not that kind of guy.

611
00:52:23,040 --> 00:52:27,440
I'm an expert pilot, trust me.
I know rivers inside out.

612
00:52:28,000 --> 00:52:32,160
All the shallows and sandbanks -
Do believe me - I can count.

613
00:52:36,280 --> 00:52:40,760
Yes, all shallows and sandbanks -
Do believe me - I can count.

614
00:53:06,080 --> 00:53:08,520
Watch out. You may run aground.

615
00:53:09,400 --> 00:53:11,360
Teaching your mother
to hatch eggs?

616
00:53:11,880 --> 00:53:13,920
I know every bank around here.

617
00:53:29,480 --> 00:53:31,600
Old devil! You boasted

618
00:53:32,080 --> 00:53:34,280
you know every bank around here.

619
00:53:34,920 --> 00:53:38,280
Of course, I know.
That's sandbank number one.

620
00:53:40,040 --> 00:53:43,160
Just you wait
till you come back.

621
00:53:44,880 --> 00:53:47,960
I am no fool to come back.

622
00:53:54,760 --> 00:53:56,840
Fifth day

623
00:54:08,020 --> 00:54:10,580
Hey buddies, come to me.

624
00:54:15,020 --> 00:54:17,140
I've come to you. Moor here.

625
00:54:23,060 --> 00:54:24,460
I've come to you.

626
00:54:33,220 --> 00:54:35,260
You can't sail without me anyway.

627
00:54:35,700 --> 00:54:38,420
- Welcome.
- You need an expert.

628
00:54:39,540 --> 00:54:41,660
Hands of gold.

629
00:54:49,020 --> 00:54:53,300
If I take it in my hands
sandbanks are no problem.

630
00:54:54,380 --> 00:54:58,340
And my own brother too, friends,
spins the yarns without end.

631
00:54:59,420 --> 00:55:01,700
Oh yes, I take it in my hands -

632
00:55:02,020 --> 00:55:03,940
Sandbanks are no problem.

633
00:55:04,740 --> 00:55:07,460
Let's overhaul the Sturgeon.

634
00:55:12,700 --> 00:55:16,180
- Left rudder!
- Don't teach me to hatch eggs.

635
00:55:16,820 --> 00:55:19,820
I know all sandbanks around here.
There's number one.

636
00:55:26,340 --> 00:55:27,700
Here's number two.

637
00:55:31,460 --> 00:55:33,300
Sixth day

638
00:55:41,100 --> 00:55:44,020
The river is wide,

639
00:55:45,940 --> 00:55:49,060
The river is blue,

640
00:55:50,980 --> 00:55:53,780
We are sailing along,

641
00:55:55,780 --> 00:55:58,900
Just me and you.

642
00:56:08,580 --> 00:56:11,940
The sky-high mountains,

643
00:56:12,860 --> 00:56:16,060
The fields under crops,

644
00:56:17,420 --> 00:56:20,460
The vast steppe expanses

645
00:56:22,100 --> 00:56:25,540
Of the land of my folks.

646
00:56:30,140 --> 00:56:33,620
We sail with ease,

647
00:56:34,820 --> 00:56:37,780
We sing with ease.

648
00:56:43,300 --> 00:56:45,860
Guys, welcome the truce envoys.

649
00:56:51,660 --> 00:56:53,060
Arrow...

650
00:57:01,620 --> 00:57:03,100
- Alyosha.
- Arrow.

651
00:57:03,180 --> 00:57:06,700
- I want to ask you something.
- I am glad you came.

652
00:57:06,980 --> 00:57:10,620
Remember the song I sang
for you on the ferry?

653
00:57:10,860 --> 00:57:12,740
Which song?

654
00:57:13,420 --> 00:57:16,460
Dunya wrote it,
our letter-carrier.

655
00:57:17,180 --> 00:57:18,820
No, I don't.

656
00:57:19,540 --> 00:57:21,860
You called her a fool.

657
00:57:22,140 --> 00:57:26,660
A fool? Now I remember.
What a fool I was.

658
00:57:26,940 --> 00:57:29,660
Right. How clever you are,
Alyosha.

659
00:57:30,420 --> 00:57:33,300
- Friends forever?
- Friends forever.

660
00:57:37,060 --> 00:57:39,540
Will you help me
with the notation.

661
00:57:39,900 --> 00:57:41,180
My pleasure.

662
00:57:42,660 --> 00:57:45,380
You are not going to present it
in Moscow, are you?

663
00:57:45,580 --> 00:57:47,500
- Yes, we are.
- You nuts or something?

664
00:57:47,740 --> 00:57:49,020
What's that for?

665
00:57:49,300 --> 00:57:52,620
You'll disgrace our region.
You'll flop for all I know.

666
00:57:53,380 --> 00:57:55,460
See that YOU don't flop.

667
00:57:55,820 --> 00:57:58,100
We'll see who's gonna flop.

668
00:57:58,340 --> 00:58:00,460
- I bet you'll flop.
- No, we won't.

669
00:58:00,780 --> 00:58:02,620
- You will.
- No, we won't.

670
00:58:02,780 --> 00:58:04,140
You will.

671
00:58:09,900 --> 00:58:12,300
Now which of us has flopped?

672
00:58:14,540 --> 00:58:18,460
How do you like it?
You'll flop indeed.

673
00:58:21,460 --> 00:58:22,820
Get her.

674
00:58:23,620 --> 00:58:25,820
She broke the boat.

675
00:58:26,980 --> 00:58:29,100
That's unprecedented hooliganism.

676
00:58:29,260 --> 00:58:31,700
She trampled on

677
00:58:32,340 --> 00:58:34,420
the newly repaired boat.

678
00:58:45,060 --> 00:58:46,820
That's ridiculous.

679
00:58:57,580 --> 00:58:59,780
I just want to fret and fume.

680
00:59:25,340 --> 00:59:28,860
Many a song has been sung
'bout the Volga.

681
00:59:32,820 --> 00:59:36,060
But the best one is yet
to be sung

682
00:59:40,260 --> 00:59:43,980
That would fly across
our Mother Volga

683
00:59:49,100 --> 00:59:52,740
In the bright rays
of our Soviet sun.

684
00:59:58,620 --> 01:00:01,740
Oh Volga, so beautiful,

685
01:00:04,260 --> 01:00:07,460
Like sea you're
full and plentiful...

686
01:00:11,780 --> 01:00:14,340
Why does he think
it's no good?

687
01:00:16,340 --> 01:00:19,140
So wide, so powerful.

688
01:00:23,180 --> 01:00:26,380
Sing a ringing
and cheerful song...

689
01:00:33,700 --> 01:00:37,500
Pride aside, if I take
a sober view of it...

690
01:00:49,140 --> 01:00:51,260
it's really bad.

691
01:00:53,340 --> 01:00:55,980
I shouldn't have hurt
his feelings.

692
01:01:44,460 --> 01:01:47,260
- Where can I find Arrow?
- Second door on the left.

693
01:01:48,020 --> 01:01:52,340
- Tugboat, ahoy!
- Tugboat, ay-ay!

694
01:01:52,740 --> 01:01:54,780
I need to talk to the cap.

695
01:01:54,980 --> 01:01:56,500
Come on, moor.

696
01:01:57,580 --> 01:02:00,260
I can't set your boat afloat,
citizen.

697
01:02:00,420 --> 01:02:02,460
I've just promised a cap.

698
01:02:02,700 --> 01:02:04,420
A cap?

699
01:02:05,460 --> 01:02:08,500
- There you are. I got you.
- It can happen to anybody.

700
01:02:09,180 --> 01:02:11,540
He's my pilot.
Let's go, comrades.

701
01:02:29,940 --> 01:02:31,860
Alyosha, can I come in?

702
01:02:32,260 --> 01:02:37,140
The concert will be broadcast
in two minutes

703
01:02:38,180 --> 01:02:40,780
without any special notice.

704
01:02:42,700 --> 01:02:43,980
Attention.

705
01:02:44,300 --> 01:02:46,060
Singer Tigrova

706
01:02:47,180 --> 01:02:49,660
will perform romance

707
01:02:50,580 --> 01:02:52,340
"Don't turn on the light"
by Arensky.

708
01:02:52,820 --> 01:02:56,100
I won't turn it on, it'll be
easier for me to speak this way.

709
01:02:59,620 --> 01:03:01,580
I told you a lie.

710
01:03:01,140 --> 01:03:03,060
I wrote this song.

711
01:03:04,620 --> 01:03:05,980
You have anybody?

712
01:03:25,100 --> 01:03:27,780
So we set your old boot
afloat, comrade chief.

713
01:03:28,060 --> 01:03:29,860
What about the sailer?

714
01:03:30,100 --> 01:03:34,540
- The sailer is not in my system.
- It is in the Soviet system.

715
01:03:35,340 --> 01:03:36,700
Later.

716
01:03:38,980 --> 01:03:40,580
Stop the boat!

717
01:03:41,380 --> 01:03:43,860
Stop the boat!

718
01:03:45,540 --> 01:03:48,380
Something must be wrong
with the steamer.

719
01:03:48,580 --> 01:03:52,460
What can be wrong with the steamer
if I am here?

720
01:03:53,260 --> 01:03:54,940
Full steam ahead.

721
01:03:55,860 --> 01:03:57,460
Fullest steam ahead!

722
01:04:00,100 --> 01:04:02,020
First day

723
01:04:06,780 --> 01:04:08,660
Second day

724
01:04:14,180 --> 01:04:16,020
Third day

725
01:04:17,420 --> 01:04:20,820
On the Greater Volga Olympiad
teams changed for Moscow boats.

726
01:04:21,300 --> 01:04:25,380
- Thanks for giving us a lift.
- Take care.

727
01:05:21,180 --> 01:05:24,380
We have moved many a mount
and river,

728
01:05:26,500 --> 01:05:30,020
Our dreams are all a-coming true.

729
01:05:32,300 --> 01:05:35,900
And the Volga now free forever,

730
01:05:39,700 --> 01:05:42,900
Carries ships to our Moscow.

731
01:06:04,820 --> 01:06:08,820
Alyosha's band was also
rehearsing a new tune.

732
01:06:14,380 --> 01:06:17,700
Sing a ringing and cheerful song

733
01:06:19,620 --> 01:06:22,940
That would show how strong we are.

734
01:06:24,980 --> 01:06:28,580
May it reach the bright golden sun,

735
01:06:31,940 --> 01:06:35,500
May it reach every person's heart.

736
01:06:50,140 --> 01:06:53,660
Like my land,

737
01:06:56,300 --> 01:06:58,340
so free

738
01:07:03,380 --> 01:07:05,380
and vast

739
01:07:13,260 --> 01:07:15,460
and strong.

740
01:07:21,380 --> 01:07:22,780
Great.

741
01:07:23,060 --> 01:07:24,940
So you say the letter-carrier
wrote it?

742
01:07:26,580 --> 01:07:27,900
Great.

743
01:07:28,340 --> 01:07:31,500
We should arrange this song,
we'll sing it in Moscow.

744
01:07:32,180 --> 01:07:33,580
Hear, hear.

745
01:07:34,220 --> 01:07:37,300
There is not any music
paper on the boat.

746
01:07:37,700 --> 01:07:40,340
Comrade Byvalov has paper galore.

747
01:07:40,740 --> 01:07:42,220
We can line it.

748
01:07:42,980 --> 01:07:44,900
Ivan Ivanovich Byvalov

749
01:07:45,620 --> 01:07:47,500
Here we are.

750
01:07:51,660 --> 01:07:53,940
Arrow, you start.

751
01:07:57,140 --> 01:08:00,980
Many a song has been sung
'bout the Volga.

752
01:08:04,940 --> 01:08:08,260
But the best one has yet
to be sung

753
01:08:11,540 --> 01:08:14,940
That would fly across
our Mother Volga

754
01:08:17,820 --> 01:08:21,020
In the bright rays
of our Soviet sun.

755
01:08:53,860 --> 01:08:56,500
Comrades!
Don't panic.

756
01:08:58,380 --> 01:09:00,100
There is no panic around here.

757
01:09:00,740 --> 01:09:04,100
There's a storm outside
and they say no panic.

758
01:09:04,580 --> 01:09:07,740
Nonsense. It's the river,
not the ocean.

759
01:09:08,940 --> 01:09:12,180
What do you know.
Rivers are worse than oceans.

760
01:09:13,100 --> 01:09:16,220
I've sailed for 30 years,
I know of heaps of stories.

761
01:09:17,420 --> 01:09:19,460
You know about wet logs?

762
01:09:19,900 --> 01:09:22,060
Wet logs?

763
01:09:22,220 --> 01:09:25,460
So you don't. You see
a log is floating.

764
01:09:26,300 --> 01:09:29,580
One half in the water,
the other on the surface.

765
01:09:30,460 --> 01:09:32,620
An inexperienced pilot
in the dark

766
01:09:32,820 --> 01:09:36,700
will run into it and damage
the bilge.

767
01:09:38,140 --> 01:09:41,180
Or the log - bang! -

768
01:09:42,340 --> 01:09:44,220
pierces the boat

769
01:09:44,340 --> 01:09:46,980
so some of it sticks out
in the saloon.

770
01:09:47,340 --> 01:09:49,460
You lie like a gas meter.

771
01:09:49,700 --> 01:09:52,380
May I not sit here if I lie.

772
01:09:55,020 --> 01:09:56,780
What did I say?

773
01:09:57,340 --> 01:09:58,900
Stand from under!

774
01:10:02,140 --> 01:10:04,180
Save who can!

775
01:10:06,500 --> 01:10:08,140
And who can't?

776
01:11:08,820 --> 01:11:10,740
The song is lost.

777
01:11:27,180 --> 01:11:30,700
Sunday

778
01:12:35,500 --> 01:12:38,380
Oh Volga so beautiful,

779
01:12:39,740 --> 01:12:42,740
Like sea you're full
and plentiful,

780
01:12:43,700 --> 01:12:46,380
Like my land free
and bountiful,

781
01:12:47,620 --> 01:12:50,500
So wide, so powerful.

782
01:12:51,580 --> 01:12:52,900
That's better.

783
01:12:53,100 --> 01:12:57,060
Let's pool our resources.
Your choir will sing it

784
01:12:57,220 --> 01:12:59,620
with our symphony orchestra.

785
01:13:00,660 --> 01:13:02,900
- Is it worth it?
- It's a good song.

786
01:13:03,380 --> 01:13:04,940
It's a wonderful song.

787
01:13:05,140 --> 01:13:07,500
Nobody knows it but we do.

788
01:13:08,580 --> 01:13:11,100
Why don't we sing it
at the Olympiad?

789
01:13:12,500 --> 01:13:15,540
We don't sing it right.
I wish Arrow were here.

790
01:13:16,300 --> 01:13:18,260
She sing. It so well.

791
01:13:19,900 --> 01:13:21,380
It's the Sturgeon.

792
01:13:22,580 --> 01:13:24,940
Moscow sea

793
01:13:33,820 --> 01:13:36,220
Arrow, I am over here.

794
01:13:47,700 --> 01:13:50,540
Forgive me, I acted
like a silly kid.

795
01:13:50,740 --> 01:13:52,900
Your Dunya is a real talent

796
01:13:53,060 --> 01:13:55,540
and her song is wonderful.

797
01:13:58,060 --> 01:13:59,980
You are laying is thick.

798
01:14:00,460 --> 01:14:03,060
Not at all. You know nothing
about music.

799
01:14:03,260 --> 01:14:05,820
I hope you didn't tell her
that I called her a fool?

800
01:14:05,980 --> 01:14:08,860
Don't hope, she heard it.

801
01:14:09,500 --> 01:14:11,820
I'll apologize to her
when I come back home.

802
01:14:12,020 --> 01:14:14,980
You don't have to, she's here.

803
01:14:15,420 --> 01:14:16,700
Here?

804
01:14:17,700 --> 01:14:19,180
Where is she?

805
01:14:19,420 --> 01:14:21,700
You are going to see her.

806
01:14:22,580 --> 01:14:24,140
I can't wait.

807
01:14:56,660 --> 01:14:59,580
Comrade Trubyshkin,
report the situation.

808
01:15:00,740 --> 01:15:02,700
You can congratulate us.

809
01:15:02,820 --> 01:15:05,820
We have a terrific number,
The Song of the Volga.

810
01:15:06,100 --> 01:15:08,540
Arrow is going to bring
the composer.

811
01:15:08,740 --> 01:15:10,580
Right. Schulbert?

812
01:15:11,860 --> 01:15:14,180
No, not Schubert, Dunya.

813
01:15:14,500 --> 01:15:16,580
She's the song writer
and Arrow's friend.

814
01:15:21,740 --> 01:15:24,820
- I don't see Dunya here.
- Open your eyes.

815
01:15:25,340 --> 01:15:26,700
Where is she?

816
01:15:27,780 --> 01:15:29,220
Right here.

817
01:15:43,260 --> 01:15:46,020
Let our enemies,
like hungry wild coyotes,

818
01:15:46,820 --> 01:15:49,660
Prowl daily 'bout our frontier,

819
01:15:50,580 --> 01:15:53,340
They will never
get to the Volga,

820
01:15:54,020 --> 01:15:56,620
Nor drink water
from that river.

821
01:15:57,940 --> 01:16:00,540
Gorblimey. How come they know it?

822
01:16:00,860 --> 01:16:03,740
Oh Volga, so beautiful,

823
01:16:04,460 --> 01:16:07,340
Like sea so full
and plentiful,

824
01:16:08,780 --> 01:16:11,540
Like my land free
and bountiful,

825
01:16:13,060 --> 01:16:15,860
So wide, so powerful.

826
01:16:17,780 --> 01:16:20,260
- It's our song.
- What do you know?

827
01:17:27,700 --> 01:17:31,020
Can you believe it?
Our song is known everywhere.

828
01:17:38,660 --> 01:17:40,980
So the music was stolen.

829
01:17:41,220 --> 01:17:43,820
Here's composer Dunya for you.

830
01:17:44,660 --> 01:17:47,860
Comrades, I swear it's her song.

831
01:17:49,380 --> 01:17:52,260
- Let me explain.
- What is there to explain?

832
01:17:52,380 --> 01:17:54,060
We put aside everything

833
01:17:54,900 --> 01:17:56,900
and rehearse this song.

834
01:17:57,100 --> 01:17:59,020
What are we going to show now?

835
01:18:11,060 --> 01:18:12,500
Moscow!

836
01:18:17,380 --> 01:18:18,780
It's curtains for me.

837
01:18:20,420 --> 01:18:22,460
This is comrade Byvalov.

838
01:18:25,220 --> 01:18:27,060
I am a reporter.

839
01:18:27,300 --> 01:18:29,460
I'd like to ask you
a few questions.

840
01:18:30,100 --> 01:18:33,260
Wait a minute. Comrade Byvalov,
they want to see you

841
01:18:33,500 --> 01:18:35,420
at the Olympiad headquarters.

842
01:18:35,780 --> 01:18:37,060
Let's go.

843
01:18:42,860 --> 01:18:45,020
What did I say?

844
01:18:48,300 --> 01:18:50,340
Greetings, comrades.

845
01:18:52,140 --> 01:18:53,900
Your Dunya--

846
01:18:54,100 --> 01:18:56,660
Don't say it.
You don't know her.

847
01:18:56,940 --> 01:18:58,940
It's her luck that I don't.

848
01:18:59,100 --> 01:19:02,340
She didn't steal the song.
It was stolen from her.

849
01:19:27,060 --> 01:19:30,140
Comrades, you see before you
the Byvalov--

850
01:19:30,700 --> 01:19:32,580
We know.

851
01:19:32,820 --> 01:19:34,820
Greetings, comrades.

852
01:19:35,020 --> 01:19:36,540
Tell us what you do.

853
01:19:39,860 --> 01:19:42,500
We make balalaikas, comrades.

854
01:19:44,020 --> 01:19:47,580
Some may think
it's nothing special.

855
01:19:48,900 --> 01:19:50,940
But I must tell you

856
01:19:51,260 --> 01:19:53,700
that given expert hands,

857
01:19:54,020 --> 01:19:56,300
this can be exciting.

858
01:19:57,860 --> 01:19:59,780
I am not boasting

859
01:20:00,420 --> 01:20:02,620
but having mastered
music culture

860
01:20:04,300 --> 01:20:06,300
and knowing Schulbert
personally--

861
01:20:07,140 --> 01:20:09,260
- Pardon?
- To the piano please.

862
01:20:11,020 --> 01:20:12,460
To the piano.

863
01:20:14,740 --> 01:20:16,300
Come on, come on.

864
01:20:19,980 --> 01:20:22,180
It's a mistake, comrades.

865
01:20:22,540 --> 01:20:25,100
My system doesn't make pianos.

866
01:20:25,460 --> 01:20:26,900
Go, go.

867
01:20:27,660 --> 01:20:30,300
Attention please.
Comrade Byvalov will perform

868
01:20:30,660 --> 01:20:32,500
his famous song.

869
01:20:36,380 --> 01:20:38,740
- I can't sing.
- Okay, play.

870
01:20:39,620 --> 01:20:42,140
- I can't play.
- Are you a poet or composer?

871
01:20:42,620 --> 01:20:45,580
I am neither, comrades,
believe me.

872
01:20:46,260 --> 01:20:47,620
Citizen...

873
01:20:47,860 --> 01:20:49,940
Is this your name?

874
01:20:50,020 --> 01:20:52,740
- Yes. The paper's mine too.
- And the notation?

875
01:20:53,100 --> 01:20:55,260
Notation? Oh yes, notation.

876
01:20:58,500 --> 01:21:00,020
I can't make head
or tail of it.

877
01:21:01,220 --> 01:21:04,020
- Do you know this song?
- Which one?

878
01:21:04,860 --> 01:21:06,620
This one.

879
01:22:17,220 --> 01:22:20,020
So many talented guys!

880
01:22:27,820 --> 01:22:30,740
So this song was written
on your paper.

881
01:22:31,140 --> 01:22:32,500
Who wrote it?

882
01:22:32,620 --> 01:22:34,260
- My--
- Yours?

883
01:22:34,460 --> 01:22:37,300
Dunya in my system
from Shallow Water.

884
01:22:37,580 --> 01:22:39,740
She must come here.

885
01:22:39,820 --> 01:22:41,820
Dunya.. And her last name?

886
01:22:42,260 --> 01:22:43,940
Last name?

887
01:22:44,260 --> 01:22:45,660
Oh, her last name.

888
01:22:47,140 --> 01:22:49,220
Let me write it down.

889
01:22:57,180 --> 01:22:59,420
Find Dunya

890
01:23:00,220 --> 01:23:04,580
from Shallow Water and send her
to the Olympiad HQ.

891
01:23:05,580 --> 01:23:07,180
Ivan Byvalov.

892
01:23:07,940 --> 01:23:10,820
- Dunya?
- Make haste. They're waiting.

893
01:23:11,180 --> 01:23:13,420
Guys, go find Dunya.

894
01:23:41,300 --> 01:23:43,100
- So you are Dunya?
- Right.

895
01:23:43,700 --> 01:23:45,700
- It's the Dunya.
- Come over here now.

896
01:23:46,100 --> 01:23:47,820
I act with a partner.

897
01:23:48,100 --> 01:23:49,420
Move it.

898
01:23:49,780 --> 01:23:52,540
- I'll help you.
- You know my tricks?

899
01:23:52,820 --> 01:23:54,860
What tricks?

900
01:23:55,500 --> 01:23:57,900
Hands of gold! Go.

901
01:24:05,460 --> 01:24:07,580
We would like you

902
01:24:07,780 --> 01:24:10,220
to sing your song.

903
01:24:10,740 --> 01:24:12,060
I beg your pardon?

904
01:24:14,380 --> 01:24:15,820
We've got her.

905
01:24:16,180 --> 01:24:18,300
- Everything's fine.
- Get her here.

906
01:24:20,620 --> 01:24:24,100
A sad mistake, comrades.

907
01:24:25,540 --> 01:24:27,580
It's not the Dunya.

908
01:24:28,060 --> 01:24:30,900
But now you'll see
the real one.

909
01:25:00,460 --> 01:25:02,020
What's that?

910
01:25:02,580 --> 01:25:04,540
- Who is she?
- Who are you?

911
01:25:04,900 --> 01:25:06,260
Me? I'm Dunya.

912
01:25:06,620 --> 01:25:08,580
- Who?
- Dunya.

913
01:25:11,140 --> 01:25:13,380
It's a coincidence.

914
01:25:15,180 --> 01:25:18,220
Tell me what's this supposed
to mean.

915
01:25:18,820 --> 01:25:22,340
They are all called Dunya.
I brought them all.

916
01:25:23,780 --> 01:25:25,740
Comrades Dunyas,

917
01:25:26,140 --> 01:25:28,420
tell me frankly

918
01:25:28,700 --> 01:25:31,500
which of you wrote this song.

919
01:25:32,100 --> 01:25:34,580
Just own it, girls.
You'll get away with it.

920
01:25:34,900 --> 01:25:36,420
They'll never own it.

921
01:25:36,820 --> 01:25:41,300
They are from Shallow Water,
they'll never own it.

922
01:25:41,860 --> 01:25:44,700
Send for Arrow.
She would know.

923
01:25:45,140 --> 01:25:47,220
- Arrow?
- What did I say?

924
01:25:47,580 --> 01:25:50,460
Why didn't you tell me earlier?
Let's go find Arrow.

925
01:25:56,620 --> 01:25:58,500
I need to go to the HQ.
Give me a boat.

926
01:25:58,900 --> 01:26:00,500
No boats at the moment.

927
01:26:00,980 --> 01:26:04,300
If you don't give me a boat,
I'll swim to the HQ.

928
01:26:04,820 --> 01:26:06,340
Arrow!

929
01:26:06,380 --> 01:26:08,220
- Where's Arrow?
- What happened?

930
01:26:08,460 --> 01:26:12,780
An emergency. It's about the song.
HQ want Arrow, now.

931
01:26:28,620 --> 01:26:30,700
Hey, come back!

932
01:26:32,700 --> 01:26:34,020
Hold on.

933
01:26:50,940 --> 01:26:53,180
Stop it. Let go of me.

934
01:26:58,500 --> 01:27:00,100
What have I done?

935
01:27:00,340 --> 01:27:02,500
- What is your name?
- Dunya Petrova..

936
01:27:02,620 --> 01:27:04,740
Who are wrecking a world record.

937
01:27:04,900 --> 01:27:06,860
I am swimming from Moscow
to Baku nonstop

938
01:27:07,020 --> 01:27:09,740
and you've pulled me out
of the water. For shame.

939
01:27:15,460 --> 01:27:17,860
It's ridiculous.

940
01:27:19,620 --> 01:27:21,700
Wait, Arrow, wait.

941
01:27:23,140 --> 01:27:24,620
Arrow!

942
01:27:25,820 --> 01:27:27,140
Wait!

943
01:27:27,940 --> 01:27:30,460
It's urgent. You are wanted
in the HQ.

944
01:27:30,660 --> 01:27:32,780
- What for?
- You should identify the girl.

945
01:27:32,980 --> 01:27:35,180
- What girl?
- The one who stole the song.

946
01:27:35,380 --> 01:27:37,260
What song?

947
01:27:39,060 --> 01:27:41,340
Oh Volga, so beautiful...

948
01:27:42,380 --> 01:27:44,340
Tell me straight:
who is this Dunya?

949
01:27:45,260 --> 01:27:46,620
It's me.

950
01:27:47,860 --> 01:27:49,140
You?

951
01:27:52,020 --> 01:27:54,380
Are you all right?

952
01:27:54,620 --> 01:27:56,020
I am all right.

953
01:28:06,140 --> 01:28:07,820
You shouldn't say it's you.

954
01:28:08,100 --> 01:28:09,980
- Yes I will.
- I won't let you.

955
01:28:10,180 --> 01:28:12,540
I am going. That's none
of your business.

956
01:28:12,740 --> 01:28:14,460
You fool, I love you.

957
01:28:16,100 --> 01:28:17,980
Are you all right?

958
01:28:18,380 --> 01:28:19,980
I am not.

959
01:28:20,700 --> 01:28:22,100
Water!

960
01:29:34,980 --> 01:29:37,220
Comrades, this citizen

961
01:29:37,660 --> 01:29:40,780
will name the Dunya
who wrote the song.

962
01:29:41,700 --> 01:29:43,140
Don't tell them.

963
01:29:43,540 --> 01:29:44,900
Hey, Dunyas.

964
01:29:53,180 --> 01:29:54,660
Comrades,

965
01:29:55,260 --> 01:29:57,460
do what you will,

966
01:29:58,540 --> 01:30:01,580
but it's me who wrote
this song.

967
01:30:07,940 --> 01:30:11,060
Many a song has been sung
'bout the Volga.

968
01:30:13,460 --> 01:30:16,900
All were mirthless
in the minor key.

969
01:30:19,660 --> 01:30:23,140
It was anguish that spawned
those melodies,

970
01:30:27,380 --> 01:30:30,500
Now it's joy and happiness
and glee.

971
01:30:34,580 --> 01:30:38,060
Sing a ringing
and cheerful song

972
01:30:41,100 --> 01:30:44,380
That would show
how strong we are.

973
01:30:46,780 --> 01:30:49,780
May it reach our golden
bright sun,

974
01:30:55,340 --> 01:30:58,340
May it reach every
person's heart.

975
01:31:01,700 --> 01:31:03,620
Listen, Arrow.

976
01:31:10,340 --> 01:31:11,780
What's that?

977
01:31:12,060 --> 01:31:14,940
It's your theme
and my arrangement.

978
01:31:38,740 --> 01:31:41,140
- Give back my striped vest.
- Let go.

979
01:31:41,500 --> 01:31:43,540
I can't go around like this.

980
01:32:08,140 --> 01:32:09,420
Comrades!

981
01:32:09,740 --> 01:32:12,500
This is the Dunya

982
01:32:12,780 --> 01:32:15,100
we've been looking for.

983
01:32:15,780 --> 01:32:18,300
She wrote this song.

984
01:32:19,460 --> 01:32:21,140
She by right

985
01:32:24,940 --> 01:32:27,100
deserves the first--

986
01:32:32,900 --> 01:32:34,220
What's going on?

987
01:33:00,020 --> 01:33:02,580
The jury calls out
Dunya Petrova,

988
01:33:03,020 --> 01:33:04,820
author of the song
of the Volga.

989
01:33:05,420 --> 01:33:07,780
The jury calls out
Dunya Petrova!

990
01:33:08,460 --> 01:33:10,220
Dunya Petrova!

991
01:33:14,660 --> 01:33:18,140
I'll never argue with you
anymore.

992
01:33:20,540 --> 01:33:22,140
- Friends?
- Friends.

993
01:33:22,340 --> 01:33:24,260
- Forever?
- Forever.

994
01:33:26,180 --> 01:33:28,780
Oh how I love you, Alyosha!

995
01:33:30,020 --> 01:33:31,860
But that's beyond
your comprehension.

996
01:33:33,340 --> 01:33:34,900
- Beyond?
- Yes, yes.

997
01:33:35,620 --> 01:33:37,660
Look, you are so obstinate.

998
01:33:39,300 --> 01:33:41,820
- Nowhere.
- Not even on the motor boat.

999
01:33:43,180 --> 01:33:44,860
- Found?
- No.

1000
01:33:45,060 --> 01:33:48,260
We can't wait any longer.
Can't you sing without her?

1001
01:33:48,620 --> 01:33:51,340
- We might but...
- Okay, come onto the stage.

1002
01:33:52,060 --> 01:33:54,740
Okhapkin, Philipp, Nina, go.

1003
01:33:56,780 --> 01:33:58,700
Come on, guys. Go, go.

1004
01:34:01,220 --> 01:34:05,300
Comrades, you will now hear
the Song of the Volga.

1005
01:34:05,820 --> 01:34:07,860
- Author!
- Where's the author?

1006
01:34:09,060 --> 01:34:11,020
Quiet, comrades.

1007
01:34:11,660 --> 01:34:14,020
If there's a song,
there's an author.

1008
01:34:15,580 --> 01:34:18,820
We dispersed every dark
thundercloud,

1009
01:34:19,820 --> 01:34:23,260
Spring has come to our
dear Motherland,

1010
01:34:23,940 --> 01:34:27,020
Like the Volga,
our life is full-blooded,

1011
01:34:27,900 --> 01:34:31,260
And this free life will not
ever end.

1012
01:34:32,300 --> 01:34:34,620
O Volga, so beautiful,

1013
01:34:40,260 --> 01:34:42,900
Like sea, you're full
and plentiful...

1014
01:34:46,020 --> 01:34:48,620
It's my throat again, Kuzma.

1015
01:34:49,020 --> 01:34:51,020
Own it, comrade Byvalov.

1016
01:34:51,180 --> 01:34:54,820
You have to study 20 years
to sing well.

1017
01:34:55,580 --> 01:34:57,300
You don't say.

1018
01:34:57,620 --> 01:35:00,140
I say... clear the deck.

1019
01:35:01,620 --> 01:35:04,220
You think I don't love you
as much as you love me?

1020
01:35:03,300 --> 01:35:05,060
Yes, I do.

1021
01:35:05,260 --> 01:35:07,260
- I love you more.
- I love you more.

1022
01:35:14,340 --> 01:35:16,100
You are mine.

1023
01:35:16,380 --> 01:35:18,220
You are another.

1024
01:35:23,020 --> 01:35:24,380
- Is that it?
- Yes.

1025
01:35:32,820 --> 01:35:34,860
- Is that it?
- Yes.

1026
01:35:35,340 --> 01:35:36,620
Arrow!

1027
01:35:38,980 --> 01:35:40,900
Hey, they caught the author.

1028
01:35:42,620 --> 01:35:44,060
Just about time.

1029
01:35:46,580 --> 01:35:48,660
Is our time up?

1030
01:35:49,220 --> 01:35:51,860
- No.
- Oh no.

1031
01:35:56,060 --> 01:35:59,220
Do not rush out of the theater,

1032
01:36:01,340 --> 01:36:03,260
We would like to keep you here

1033
01:36:03,820 --> 01:36:06,180
For another couple minutes

1034
01:36:06,380 --> 01:36:08,700
To strike balances, Oh yes.

1035
01:36:19,700 --> 01:36:22,420
We tried real hard,

1036
01:36:24,820 --> 01:36:27,060
We are glad you laughed,

1037
01:36:32,740 --> 01:36:36,580
For laughter can heal,
And laughter can kill.

1038
01:36:37,700 --> 01:36:41,820
This is not to say red tapists
Can be found at every turn.

1039
01:36:42,860 --> 01:36:46,820
When you see those opportunists,
Like Byvalov they are all.

1040
01:36:47,660 --> 01:36:51,540
Very oft petty thoughts and actions,
Aftermath of the cursed time,

1041
01:36:52,500 --> 01:36:56,460
Do obstruct our work and creations,
Bloom of talent in our clime.

1042
01:36:57,540 --> 01:37:00,340
We must clear all the rubbish,

1043
01:37:02,220 --> 01:37:05,340
Sweep it off with our hands

1044
01:37:10,220 --> 01:37:14,260
And wide as the Volga
along the road

1045
01:37:15,100 --> 01:37:18,260
March from strength to strength.

1046
01:37:19,220 --> 01:37:22,340
O Volga, so beautiful,

1047
01:37:24,140 --> 01:37:27,140
Like sea, you're full
and plentiful,

1048
01:37:28,620 --> 01:37:31,580
Like my land free
and bountiful,

1049
01:37:32,940 --> 01:37:35,620
So wide, deep and powerful.

1050
01:37:48,180 --> 01:37:50,060
Translated by Raisa Svirina

